I have three problems after doing the basic Squiffy tutorials.

1. Link classes
I would like to be able to display passage links and section links in a slightly different way. They play different roles, but they look the same. Both have class &quot;squiffy-link&quot;. How to add class &quot;passage&quot; to passage links and &quot;section&quot; to section links? As a result, the HTML would look something like below, and it would be possible to style both links differently in CSS:

[code:11f4wn38]&lt;p&gt;Looking around the room, you can see a &lt;a class=&quot;squiffy-link link-passage&quot; data-passage=&quot;TV&quot;&gt;TV&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a class=&quot;squiffy-link  link-passage&quot; data-passage=&quot;book&quot;&gt;book&lt;/a&gt; and a piece of &lt;a class=&quot;squiffy-link  link-passage&quot; data-passage=&quot;paper&quot;&gt;paper&lt;/a&gt; with some handwriting scribbled on it&#46;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to have the &lt;a class=&quot;squiffy-link  link-section&quot; data-section=&quot;roast chicken&quot;&gt;roast chicken&lt;/a&gt; or skip straight to &lt;a class=&quot;squiffy-link  link-section&quot; data-section=&quot;dessert&quot;&gt;dessert&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;[/code:11f4wn38]

2. Section names
Here is my short story:

[code:11f4wn38]Do you want to see the &#91;&#91;first_section&#93;&#93;, the &#91;&#91;second section&#93;&#93;(second_section) or skip straight to &#91;&#91;dessert&#93;&#93;?

&#91;&#91;first_section&#93;&#93;&#58;
This is the first section&#46;

&#91;&#91;second_section&#93;&#93;&#58;
This is the second section&#46;

&#91;&#91;dessert&#93;&#93;&#58;
Three different flavours of ice cream - yum![/code:11f4wn38]

Upon compilation, it fires an error: 
[quote:11f4wn38]Squiffy 2.1
Loading J:\squiffy\error1\error1.squiffy
Writing story.js
WARNING: J:\squiffy\error1\error1.squiffy line 3: In section &quot;_default&quot; there is a link to a section called [
[second section&lt;/a&gt; or skip straight to [[dessert]], which doesn't exist
Writing index.html
Writing style.css
Done.[/quote:11f4wn38]

And the result HTML file is messed. What is wrong with the code? 

3. Javascript

This is my another short story:

[code:11f4wn38]Do you want to see a &#91;&#91;javascript demo&#93;&#93;(js_demo)?
&#91;&#91;js_demo&#93;&#93;&#58;
Clicking this &#91;link&#93; will show an alert&#46;

&#91;link&#93;&#58;
	alert (&quot;Hello!&quot;);

Text for the passage&#46;[/code:11f4wn38]

There is one &quot;tab&quot; before the word &quot;alert&quot;. After running it and clicking, it just displays text 'alert (&quot;Hello!&quot;)' in &quot;pre&quot; tags, instead of calling a javascript alert function. Like this: [attachment=0:11f4wn38]<!-- ia0 -->prtscr3.jpg<!-- ia0 -->[/attachment:11f4wn38]
